body:
The list of webpack versions I tested:
5.12.3 ok
5.15.0 ok
5.17.0 ok
5.18.0 ok
5.19.0 ok
5.20.0 error
5.20.2 error
5.30.0 error

I know discovered that the bug seems to be related to the `concatenateModules` optimization settings.
When setting `optimization.concatenateModules` to `false` the generated code works again.

with this settings the generated line that works as expected looks likes this:
```js
(0,Source_ODS_types__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__/* .checkIsNonemptyString */ .hy)(buttonName, 'buttonName');
```

rename.from: Possible major problem in production mode starting with webpack 5.20.0 up to 5.30.0
rename.to: Failing code when using concatenateModules option starting with webpack 5.20.0 up to 5.30.0

Sure:
[source.zip](https://github.com/webpack/webpack/files/6266524/source.zip)

I'm happy to help, if you could share what kind of error in our code you suspect is causing this problem.

All I noticed, is the difference in how the generated code references the imported modules:

The problem identifies the modules by using a (local) variable `types` and the variable seems to be undefined:
```js
(0,types/* checkIsNonemptyString */.hy)(buttonName, 'buttonName');
```

But in locations that do not cause an exception functions from the same `types.ts` module are referenced by using `Source_ODS_types__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_1__`:
```js
(0,Source_ODS_types__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_1__/* .checkIsString */ .Nk)(stringToConvert, 'stringToConvert');
```

It's difficult to find the problem without a repro.

Renaming the file should not make any difference to the concatenation. But the filename has influence on the concatenation:

When choosing variable names for default exports, namespace objects or in case of variable name conflicts, the basename of the file is used as starting name. Usually we detect existing variable names in the modules and avoid them, but maybe there is some bug here and there does happen a conflict nonetheless, which causes this weird behavior.

It would be really helpful to get the generation code from the bundle. Maybe you can make a diff of the bundle between `types.ts` and `typecheck.ts`?

I can no longer reproduce the variant with the name change probably just made a mistake when testing.
